OL,3,CGovernment orders review into role of
OL,4,Cphysician associates in the NHS
OL,6,FThere are currently around 3,500
OL,7,Fphysician associates and anaesthesia
OL,8,Fassociates working in the NHS in
OL,9,FEngland, but the health service's Long
OL,10,FTerm Workforce Plan aims to increase
OL,11,Fthat to 10,000 by 2037.
OL,13,FPhysician Associates and Anaesthesia
OL,14,FAssociates should work under the
OL,15,Fsupervision of doctors in hospitals
OL,16,Fand GP practices.
OL,18,FThey must complete a three-year
OL,19,Fhealth, biomedical or science
OL,20,Fundergraduate degree, followed by two
OL,21,Fyears of postgraduate medical training.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
